{"experiment_id": "synthetic_benign", "epoch": 13, "role": "user", "artifact_class": "Commit", "identifier": ["spring-projects", "spring-boot", "8677496ea30b4edcbc48a45593c3c5eb52af4e83"], "url": "https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/commit/8677496ea30b4edcbc48a45593c3c5eb52af4e83", "semantic_text": "ZIP functions correctly when their names in graph and in Python differ (#144)\n\nWhen running functions from ZIP we need to import them not using their\nnames in graphs but using their Python names. These names can differ\neasily e.g. because Python code style is different from the one\ncustomers want to use in the graph, e.g.\n\n```\nclass AStarSearch(TensorlakeFunction):\n  name = \"find_shortest_path\"\n\n  def run(self):\n     pass\n```\n\nThe importable Python class name of a function differs depending on how\nits class was created.\nClasses created manually by inheriting from TensorlakeCompute exist in\ntheir module source code and thus they can be imported directly by class\nname.\nClasses created dynamically by decorators like @tensorlake_function need\nto use the original Python function name which is decorated by the\ndecorator. When loading such function from the zipped source the\ndecorator will re-create the class with same same name as the original\nfunction.", "semantic_meaning": null, "semantic_ref": null, "semantic_label": "benign", "semantic_content_type": "real", "timestamp": 1629249927.0}
