{"experiment_id": "synthetic_benign", "epoch": 16, "role": "user", "artifact_class": "Commit", "identifier": ["spring-projects", "spring-boot", "fa6232a70d356cd4993bfa2427aef2c9c944709e"], "url": "https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/commit/fa6232a70d356cd4993bfa2427aef2c9c944709e", "semantic_text": "Package Graph code source into ZIP and run it in Function Executor (#140)\n\nThis removes CloudPickle code serialization which is known to have\nmany problems. The ZIP functionality covered well with integration\ntests that document expected behaviors.\n\nAlso refactored `tensorlake deploy` code to split into Tensorlake\nCloud specific and generic OSS parts. The OSS part includes\nworkflow file info collection functions. Tensorlake Cloud specific\ncode uses the collected info to do actual deployments and specific\nvalidations.\n\nTested `tensorlake deploy` manually in dev with and without\nimage builder v2.\n\nAlso fixed Python code constructs that don't work on Python 3.9.\n\nAnd fixed a bug where we were using only a single image build\ncontext per Image when Builder v2 is used. This fixes bug when\nmultiple functions use the same image but with the bug only\none function will be able to run.", "semantic_meaning": null, "semantic_ref": null, "semantic_label": "benign", "semantic_content_type": "real", "timestamp": 1629249930.0}
